	<div id="contenu">
		<h1>Step 2: Modeling and simulating deformations</h1>
		
		The second step of this tutorial is to allow the finger to be mechanically simulated. This implies to:
		<UL>
                    <LI>Provide a solving method</LI>
                    <LI>A volumetric mesh and mass properties to compute deformations and energy</LI>
                    <LI>A mechanical model of the deformation</LI>
                    <LI>An attach point.</LI>
              	</UL>
		
		<p>Additionnaly, a visual model has been added, with a mapping to provide visualization of the deformations produced.</p>
		
		<center><img src="../data/images/Finger_0.png"/></center>

		<h2>How to use the demo</h2>
		<p>After clicking on "Animate" you can select the finger (shift + click left) and move it around.</p>
	
